02/12/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian Human Rights Minister Rasim Ljajic asked the war crimes tribunal in The Hague on Wednesday (1 December) to transfer the "Vukovar trio" cases to Serbia. In a letter to Tribunal President Theodor Meron and chief prosecutor Carla del Ponte, Ljajic suggested the transfer would have a positive effect on Serbia's relationship with the tribunal. (B92 - 01/12/04)
